                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.52/194.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Letcher</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Chihuahua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-03-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 16, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s February 25. Military Governor Chao replies on behalf of General
                    Villa to my note directed to the latter urging an investigation of the killing
                    of Jose and Agustin Gonzalez that the state government is not authorized under
                    orders prevailing to treat on matters of international bearing and that
                    questions of this character should be addressed to the First Chief of the
                    revolution.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Letcher</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
